The paper discusses the use of ensembles of neural networks for estimating predictive uncertainty, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of probabilistic modeling (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian neural networks (BNNs) and the departure from Bayesian methodology in traditional ensembling methods, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ensembling in computer vision (cs.CV) and system engineering (cs.SY) applications.
